                                                                                                                         5                                                                                        THE ARTS                                                    
	AMRITA SHER-GIL: A SELF-PORTRAIT IN LETTERS AND WRITINGS (2 VOLUMES) (Tulika)               
	Dead at 28 and signing off her letters to her father as Your sinful daughter, Amri, could she have been a more dazzling writer than a painter, had she lived longer?                    
	SARIS OF INDIA: TRADITION AND BEYOND (Roli)
   By Rita Kapur Chishti              
	Bharat darshan through the wonder of familiar drapes. How the versatility and sensuousness of the sari have fascinated wearer and viewer through the ages.                    
	PICASSO (Monacelli) 
  By Philippe Dagen               
	An inexhaustible master and the monsters of his mind. Solidly historicist without getting carried away by erudition.                    
	THE NINTH: BEETHOVEN AND THE WORLD IN 1824 (Faber)
  By Harvey Sachs               
	An analysis of one of the great  perhaps greatest  pieces of Western classical music. Provides the social and intellectual background to the music as well as an interpretation in terms of Beethovens overall creativity.                    
	CINEMA, EMERGENCE, AND THE FILMS OF SATYAJIT RAY (University of California)
   By Keya Ganguly               
	Complicates and enriches our understanding of Ray. In spite of the jargon, a critically informed revisiting of a familiar corpus.                                                                                                                                                            
